msgstr ""

#: ../../rst/scenario_guides/guide_kubernetes.rst:44
msgid ""
"By default the OpenShift Rest Client will look for ``~/.kube/config``, "
"and if found, connect using the active context. You can override the "
"location of the file using the``kubeconfig`` parameter, and the context, "
"using the ``context`` parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rst/scenario_guides/guide_kubernetes.rst:46
msgid ""
"Basic authentication is also supported using the ``username`` and "
"``password`` options. You can override the URL using the ``host`` "
"parameter. Certificate authentication works through the ``ssl_ca_cert``, "
"``cert_file``, and ``key_file`` parameters, and for token authentication,"
" use the ``api_key`` parameter."
msgstr ""

